      "raw_text": "\n\n\nWASHINGTON, Feb. 15.-\"The\nonly conservation legislation that\nwill be passed at this session Of\ncongress\" according to a member\nof the house today, will be gen.\neral classification bill, bill for the\nwithdrawal Of certain lands and the\nreclamation bond issue act\"\n\n\n1t will be necessary for support\ners of the reclamation bond issue to\nfight hard to get the bill through\nthe house, according to the report.\nThe indications at present are\nthese three measures will be the\nlimit on which the leaders can\nagree in connection with President\nTaft's conservation program.\n\n\nThere is possibility also that\none of these may fail of passage."
